    "ip_morale_text",
    "Morale_represents_the_ability_and_willingness_of_the_troops_in_a_party_to_summon_up_the_endurance,_bravery,_and_discipline_they_need_to_face_the_stresses_of_battle_and_the_march._It_is_not_the_same_thing_as_the_troops'_happiness._Elite_troops_may_grumble_and_whine_about_the_hardships_of_campaigning_--_but_then_stand_together_as_one_when_the_arrows_start_to_fly._On_the_other_hand,_a_commander_who_gives_his_men_everything_they_want_may_find_that_they_grow_soft,_and_waiver_before_the_enemy's_charge.^^Morale's_greatest_impact_is_on_a_party's_behavior_in_battle,_determining_how_aggressively_troops_engage_the_enemy,_and_how_likely_they_are_to_break_and_run_if_they_perceive_the_tide_of_battle_turning_against_them._Morale_also_affects_a_party's_march_speed,_as_a_less_motivated_party_will_move_more_slowly,_as_the_men_are_not_pushing_themselves_to_their_physical_limit,_and_pause_more_frequently,_as_it_waits_for_stragglers_to_catch_up._Finally,_a_party_with_very_low_morale_will_start_to_suffer_desertions.^^Some_factors_that_affect_morale_are_intuitive._For_example,_a_charismatic_commander_with_a_reputation_for_winning_battles_can_infuse_his_or_her_men_with_a_sense_of_confidence._Leaders_who_give_their_men_well_ample_and_varied_supplies_of_food,_and_pay_them_on_time,_demonstrate_that_they_care_about_their_troops'_welfare_and_are_less_likely_to_lead_them_into_disaster.^^Other_factors_are_less_intuitive_--_particularly_those_related_to_a_party's_sense_of_group_cohesion._In_a_small_tight-knit_party,_for_example,_men_will_often_fight_hard_against_daunting_odds_to_avoid_showing_cowardice_before_their_comrades-in-arms._A_large_party_on_the_other_hand_may_see_its_cohesion_strained,_as_the_commander_has_less_time_to_supervise_the_men,_listen_to_their_grievances,_and_resolve_their_disputes._Frequent_battles_will_strengthen_the_bonds_between_men,_while_long_periods_without_combat_will_see_the_troops_become_bored_and_quarrelsome.^^The_morale_report,_accessible_by_hitting_the_'Party_Info'_button_on_the_'Character'_screen,_will_give_the_player_a_sense_of_the_factors_affecting_his_or_her_men's_morale.",
    "士气让部队中的士兵们保持坚忍不拔，勇往直前，和纪律严明的能力和积极性，这些都是他们抵御战斗和行军当中的压力所必需的。这个和士兵们的愉悦度不是一回事情。精锐部队也许会因不满而抱怨战役的艰苦——但是当他们面对如蝗飞矢的时候还是会坚如磐石团结如一。另一方面，一个无微不至给予他的部下任何需求的指挥官，也许反而会发现他们变得软弱，并且在敌人进攻前就望风而逃。^^士气最大的影响是对于部队在战斗中的行为，决斗了士兵与敌人交战时有多凶猛，以及当他们发现战场形势不对时有多想落荒而逃。士气同样影响一支部队的行军速度，越没有动力的队伍跑的就越慢，因为这种情况下部下不会尽力而为，并且经常要停下来休息，所以经常要等掉队的人赶上来。最终，一支士气低下的部队就会有人开小差逃走。^^一些影响士气的因素是很直观的。比如，一个魅力过人并且百战百胜的指挥官可以给他或者她的部下在精神上以极大的鼓舞。给部下提供大量而又丰富食物，并且不拖欠部下佣金的领袖们，表现的很关心他们的士兵的福利，并且不喜欢带领他们深赴险地。^^另外一些因素就不是那么直观了——特别是那些涉及部队的团队凝聚力方面的。例如，在一支精兵队伍里，个个都会和优势兵力的敌人艰苦作战毫不畏缩，因为你的胆小与否别人都能看得到。相对的面对一支庞大的队伍你也许就会看到其内部团结有问题，这是由于指挥官没有更多的时间来监督部下，倾听他们的抱怨，并且解决他们之间的争端。频繁的战事将使战士们团结，而长时间的无所事事会使士兵们变得无聊和相互争吵。^^通过点击“报告”按钮来显示的士气报告，将给玩家显示哪些因素正在影响他或她部下的士气。"
