    "ip_politics_text",
    "The_realms_of_the_Northlands,_although_they_represent_different_cultures,_all_shared_a_basic_political_system_that_preceded_feudalism._At_the_top_of_Germanic_social_hierarchy_was_the_king,_elected_by_a_council_of_noblemen_from_the_royal_house._All_the_land_of_the_realm_belonged_to_the_king,_who_distributed_it_among_the_aristocracy_and_the_warriors_who_had_performed_outstanding_deeds._This_land_however_did_not_become_their_property_and_in_case_of_death,_either_the_king_or_the_client,_returned_to_the_ruler._The_nobility_governed_each_shire_in_king's_name_with_the_responsibility_for_administration_and_justice,_raising_and_leading_the_levies_of_men_to_the_battlefield._For_this_purpose_they_divided_their_land_into_smaller_parcels_among_the_freemen_who_formed_the_backbone_of_the_rural_economy_of_the_kingdom._These_farmers_and_householders_paid_rent_to_their_overlord_and/or_had_several_duties_with_him,_such_as_building_fortifications_or_working_some_days_of_the_week_during_the_harvest-time.^^This_system_of_clientship_was_also_practised_between_nobles,_which_established_hierarchies_of_homage_and_political_support._The_increasingly_powerful_monasteries_were_autonomous_ecclesiastical_establishments_with_their_own_land_and_clients.^^A_distinctive_feature_of_the_Celtic_societies_(Gaelic,_Welsh_and_Pictish)_was_the_importance_of_the_corporate_lineage-group,_the_clan._A_large_group_of_related_people_supposedly_descended_from_one_common_ancestor,_acting_as_an_independent_social_and_legal_entity.^^When_one_realm_in_the_Northlands_makes_war_on_another,_the_political_unity_of_each_kingdom_is_as_important_as_the_quality_or_number_of_its_soldiers_in_determining_the_outcome._In_a_cohesive_kingdom,_nobles_will_join_together_in_a_large_force_to_sweep_their_opponents_before_them._In_a_kingdom_divided_by_petty_quarrels,_lords_will_fail_to_respond_to_the_marshal's_summons,_or_drift_away_to_attend_to_their_own_business_if_a_campaign_is_not_going_well._A_faction's_political_cohesion_will_also_impact_warfare_when_campaigns_are_not_in_progress._In_a_divided_faction,_lords_will_be_less_likely_to_join_together_on_raids_and_patrols_or_to_come_to_each_other's_defense.^^If_it_seems_nobles'_bickering_and_quarrels_are_self-defeating_when_the_enemy_is_just_around_the_corner,_keep_in_mind_that_ultimately,_a_noble's_loyalty_doesn't_belong_to_a_particular_faction_or_culture,_but_to_himself_and_to_his_family._If_a_noble_fears_that_his_faction_is_collapsing,_or_if_he_is_being_neglected_by_his_liege,_he_can_usually_find_a_reason_to_withdraw_his_oath_of_allegiance_and_change_sides._Players_should_keep_this_in_mind,_as_they_may_find_that_there_are_opportunities_to_turn_discontented_former_enemies_into_allies.",
    "北地诸国，尽管拥有各自不同的文化，但都实行着一个早于封建制的政治体系。在日耳曼社会中，最高的统治者是国王。而国王是由贵族组成的议会选举产生。王国所有的土地都属于国王，国王则把土地分给贵族和对王国有贡献的人。但这些土地并不是他们的私有的，在他们死后，都会被收归国王。贵族们以国王的名义确保每块领地的统治和公正，并在战时带领征召兵前往战场。为了这个目的，贵族们又把土地分给那些能够发展农村经济的自由民。而这些平时种田畜牧的人又得向他们的领主赋税并履行一些义务，诸如兵役，城堡建设等活动。^^这种情况很普遍，各级贵族们也是如此。而逐渐强大的修道院则对它的教区实行自治。^^不同的是，在凯尔特社会中（盖尔，威尔士和皮克特），他们更注重血缘，氏族。是一个由一群拥有相同祖先的同族人组成的独立社会。^^当北地的某个国家和别国开战，各个王国内部在政治上是否团结，严重影响到其能够决定战争结果的士兵的质量和数量。在一个团结的王国，贵族们会联合在一起成为一股强大的力量扫除他们面前的对手。在一个因为喋喋不休的争论而四分五裂的王国里，领主们将不听从元帅的召集，或者在一场战役如果进行的并不顺利的时候四散而去忙他们自己的事情。一个阵营政治上的凝聚力还会在战役没有进行的情况下导致军事冲突。在一个分裂的阵营，领主们在出击和巡逻的时候不大愿意联合行动，还有共同防御。^^如果发现领主们在敌人出现在地平线上的时候因为斗嘴和争论而要弄巧成拙，记住——从根本上讲，一名贵族的忠诚不是对于特定的阵营或者文化，而是对于他自己以及他的家族。如果一个贵族担心他的阵营崩溃，或者是他正在被他的君主忽视，他通常会找个理由撤销他效忠的宣誓，然后投奔别处。玩家要记住这一点，因为你有机会让心中不满的前敌人转变成盟友。"
