    "ip_military_campaigns_text",
    "When_kingdoms_in_the_Northlands_go_to_war,_their_armies_have_two_basic_offensive_options._They_can_try_to_attack_villages_and_lay_waste_to_the_countryside,_damaging_their_enemy's_prestige_and_economy._Or,_they_can_try_to_seize_and_hold_castles_or_towns,_taking_territory._The_second_option_can_involve_long,_bloody_sieges,_but_will_yield_more_decisive_results.^^It_is_important_to_note_that_the_realms_of_the_Northlands_do_not_field_standing_armies,_which_remain_in_the_field_as_long_as_the_ruler_desires._Rather,_the_realms_of_the_Northlands_are_protected_by_the_nobles,_their_companions,_and_the_feudal_levies_they_raise.__Sometimes,_these_nobles_launch_their_own_private_attacks_into_enemy_territory,_but_the_most_decisive_events_will_usually_take_place_when_the_great_hosts_are_assembled._The_kingdom's_marshal,_a_noble_appointed_by_the_king,_will_summon_the_host_before_the_campaign_and_lead_them_out_to_battle._However,_he_should_be_careful_not_to_keep_them_in_the_field_for_too_long._Otherwise,_the_host_will_begin_to_disintegrate,_as_the_vassals_drift_off_to_pursue_their_own_business,_and_the_army_will_be_vulnerable_to_a_counter-attack.^^For_this_reason,_the_rhythm_of_wars_in_the_Northlands_often_resemble_the_rhythm_of_a_duel_between_two_individual_combatants._One_side_will_gather_its_strength_and_seek_to_land_a_blow_against_the_enemy's_territory._If_the_marshal_spends_too_little_time_gathering_the_vassals,_he_may_not_be_able_to_do_any_real_damage._If_he_spends_too_much_time,_then_the_campaign_may_end_before_it_has_even_begun._A_large_realm_will_have_an_advantage_over_a_smaller_one,_just_as_a_brawny_combatant_has_an_edge_over_a_smaller_foe,_but_a_realm's_political_cohesion_can_also_be_a_factor,_just_as_a_fighter_with_great_stamina_can_outlast_her_opponent._Sometimes,_the_armies_of_two_realms_will_meet_head_on,_resulting_in_a_major_battle_in_which_both_numbers_and_morale_will_decide_the_outcome.^^Kingdoms_will_have_imperfect_intelligence_about_their_enemies._Attacking_lords_will_need_to_frequently_scout_enemy_territory_to_determine_which_fortresses_may_be_vulnerable._An_army_defending_its_homeland_will_benefit_from_the_alarms_raised_by_castles_and_towns,_which_broadcast_intelligence_about_enemy_movements_in_the_area._Such_intelligence_will_be_imprecise,_however,_particularly_when_it_comes_to_numbers._A_defending_force_which_sets_out_to_raise_a_siege_or_rescue_a_village_may_be_able_to_overwhelm_an_unprepared_attacker_--_or_it_may_miscalculate,_and_find_that_it_is_the_one_to_be_overwhelmed._Attackers,_in_turn,_must_be_careful_how_far_they_advance_into_enemy_territory,_with_aggressive_marshals_venturing_further_than_cautious_ones.^^Players_will_be_expected_to_join_in_their_faction's_military_campaign,_either_by_joining_the_host,_or_by_scouting_ahead_into_enemy_territory._Some_players_may_find_that_their_realm's_marshal_is_too_cautious,_or_too_aggressive,_for_their_tastes._In_this_case,_they_can_intrigue_with_other_lords_to_try_to_replace_the_marshal,_or_build_support_to_become_the_marshal_themselves.^^Most_wars_are_of_limited_duration._A_king_who_goes_to_war_will,_for_the_sake_of_honor,_feel_obligated_to_pursue_the_conflict_for_a_short_while._However,_unless_he_is_soundly_beating_his_enemy,_he_may_soon_start_looking_for_a_way_out_of_the_conflict,_lest_he_leave_himself_vulnerable_to_an_attack_by_a_third_party._The_Northlands'_rulers_are_keenly_aware_that_today's_ally_may_be_tomorrow's_enemy,_and_vice_versa.",
    "当北地诸王国开始战事，他们的军队有两种基本的进攻方式。他们会试图进攻村庄并摧毁它，破坏敌人的声望和经济。或者，他们可以试图夺取并占据城堡或者城镇，扩张领土。这第二种方式包括长期，血腥的围攻，但是能产生更有决定性的成果。^^得记住很重要的一点在北地的国家里没有按照统治者要求常驻各处的常备军。相对的，不列颠各国由权臣贵族及其各自从属所招募的封建佣兵所保护。有时候，这些贵族私自发动对敌人领土的进攻，但决定性的攻击总是发生在大规模军团被召集的时候。各个王国的元帅，一名由国王指派的贵族，会在战役开始前召集军团并率领他们投入战斗。然而，他也需要注意别让他们过于恋战。否则，军团就会开始瓦解，因为那些领主会各自离开去忙他们自己的事情，而大军就会变得容易遭受对方的反击。^^因此，在北地，战争的节奏通常就像是两个单独的战斗者之间的决斗一样。一方会纠集自己的力量寻求对敌方领土的一次猛攻。如果元帅仓促间集结领主们的时间过短，他就不能实施任何有效的攻击。如果他花的时间过长，那战役也许会在还没开始之前就结束。大国对小国拥有优势，就像一名强壮的战士比弱小的对手要厉害，但是一个国家政治上的凝聚力也不能忽视，就像一个耐力过人的斗士会比他的对手活得更久。有时候，两个国家的军队会迎头碰上，军队的士气和数量将决定这场大决战的结果。^^王国们对于其敌人总是缺乏情报。进攻方的领主需要频繁地侦查敌人的领土来决定哪个要塞也许易于攻击。守卫本土的军队会有从城堡和城镇得到警报的优势，它们会传播敌人在其附近行动的情报。然而，这些情报并不精确，特别是对于敌军的数量方面。解围或者援救村庄的防守方也许能击败一支没有准备的进攻部队——或者失算，成为被打败的一方。而对于进攻方，必须要小心他们深入敌后有多远，而好战的元帅要比谨慎的元帅更冒险。^^玩家会期望加入其阵营的军事战役，比如加入军团，或者打头阵去敌人领土侦查。某些玩家也许会发现他们国家的元帅个人风格太谨慎了，或者太好战了。这种情况下，他们可以串通其他领主来试图更换元帅，或者寻求支持来自己当上元帅。^^大部分战争持续有限的一段时间。一名想要开战的国王，为了荣耀，觉得有义务短时间里解决冲突。然而，除非他狠揍了敌人一顿。他也许很快开始寻求平息冲突的途径，以免自己暴露在第三方部队的攻击威胁之下。北地的统治者们都清楚地明白今天的盟友也许明天就会成为敌人，反之亦然。"
